💡 Placement Tip

Most placement questions on GP involve finding the common ratio, the nth term, the sum of n terms, or identifying whether a sequence is a GP. Learn the formulas Tₙ = a × r⁽ⁿ⁻¹⁾, Sₙ = a(rⁿ − 1)/(r − 1), and S∞ = a/(1 − r) (for |r| < 1). Also memorize common powers such as 2⁵ = 32, 3⁵ = 243, and 5⁴ = 625 to solve questions much faster during placement aptitude tests.
